text=In [[http://stackoverflow.com/questions/135688/setting-environment-variables-in-os-x]], the general consensus is to change the @@/etc/launch.conf@@ file. The simplest way is to use the @@launchctl@@ command:%0a%0a(:source lang=bash:)%0asudo launchctl setenv PATH /usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/opt/local/bin:/opt/local/sbin:/bin:/sbin:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0aOne can also set the path by putting the command in the @@/etc/launch.conf@@ file:%0a%0a(:source:)%0asetenv PATH /usr/local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/opt/local/bin:/opt/local/sbin:/bin:/sbin:/usr/bin:/usr/sbin%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Summary:a quick `HowTo to setting environment variables in OSX:)%0a(:Parent:(Technology.)OSX:)%0a(:IncludeMe:[[(Technology.)OSX]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!HowTos]]:)%0a(:Tags: mac, osx, sysadmin:)%0a(:tags-hide mac, osx, sysadmin :)%0a%0a%0a
